// What is the return value of map in the following code? Why?

let result = ['ant', 'bear'].map(elem => {
  if (elem.length > 3) {
    return elem;
  }
});
console.log(result);

// Solution: The return output is [undefined, 'bear']. The return value of
// map is an array, which is the collection type that map always returns.

// When a function doesn't explicitly return something, it implicitly returns
// undefined.

// Thus, the first element of caller, 'ant', evaluates as false by the callback
// function.